Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please start your clocks
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.50,0:07:56.02,Background,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:00.18,Background,,0,0,0,,Mr. Shinoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This year's pro exam's started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.38,0:08:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The preliminaries are going on right\Nnow, and the finals will be in a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.84,0:08:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Are Kadowaki-kun and Isumi-kun the favorites?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.66,0:08:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen Isumi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.60,0:08:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks much more confident. He's\Nnothing like he was last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.99,0:08:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds hopeful. He had a fragileness\Nabout him last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.59,0:08:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Amano-san, people speak as if you need\Nto bloom early in the Go world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.12,0:08:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've always believed that everyone\Nhas their own pace for growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking the long way isn't always bad in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Shinoda, do you mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.85,0:08:53.94,Background,,0,0,0,,if I use those words in an article\Nif Isumi-kun passes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.12,0:08:59.81,Background,,0,0,0,,Ochi-kun and Waya-kun, who passed\Nlast year... they're working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.31,0:09:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Shindou-kun seems to have won\Nhis first comeback game, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like those who pass this\Nyear to be just like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:10.76,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Black won't let me off that easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.42,0:10:13.25,Thinking,,0,0,0,,White will have a tough time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:41.54,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:45.08,Thinking,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect him to strike back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.76,0:11:02.89,Thinking,,0,0,0,,It's over if I let Black eliminate\Nall of my Aji with one Tsuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:09.40,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Now black has nothing to worry about, the\Ngame's going to become one-sided...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:21.91,Ed5Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\1c&H0700D6&\blur1\frz270\fs38\bord0\pos(390,31)}By Resignation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:21.91,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&H000000&\fs32\blur1\fscy95\shad0\bord0\pos(327,420)}{\i1}Shindou{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:21.91,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&H000000&\fs32\blur1\fscy95\shad0\bord0\pos(508,420)}{\i1}Tsujioka{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.69,0:11:30.80,Thinking,,0,0,0,,He won against not only Murakami-kun,\Nbut Tsujioka-kun as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:35.34,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Is the new wave really coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.26,0:11:39.35,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Is Shindou-Kun's strength the real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:46.64,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(626,626)\pos(320,431)}Second match of the Second preliminaries for the Ouza Match
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.15,0:11:54.61,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(626,626)\pos(320,431)}Touya Akira 3-dan
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:06.12,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(501,626)\pos(320,431)}Matsunaga Toshiyuki 6-dan
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I resign.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:12.84,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(542,584)\pos(320,431)}First round of the second preliminaries for the Tengen match
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:28.52,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(501,626)\pos(320,431)}Touya Akira 3-dan
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.19,0:12:40.86,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(542,584)\pos(320,431)}Kamimaezu Hiroshi 7-dan
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.47,0:13:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I resign
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.15,0:13:09.62,Thinking,,0,0,0,,He's defeating high dan players...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.52,0:13:12.60,Thinking,,0,0,0,,one after another...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.69,0:13:19.11,Thinking,,0,0,0,,The new wave may really be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.76,0:13:21.61,Thinking,,0,0,0,,With Touya Akira in the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.17,0:13:35.54,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\bord1\fs21\fscx101\fad(542,584)\pos(320,431)}Fifth Game of the Gosei Match
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I resign
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Master Ogata.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.03,0:14:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only Jyudan, but a second title as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.14,0:14:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.28,0:14:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Nogi, looking back on the game\Njust now, how do you feel about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He stuck in and pushed me past the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.21,0:14:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.81,0:14:14.46,Background,,0,0,0,,How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.48,0:14:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that you defended the Meijin title three\Nconsecutive times ten years ago, Nogi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But now you're getting defeated\Nby the likes of Ogata-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.74,0:14:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Kuwabara...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.53,0:14:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched your game in another room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.93,0:14:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nogi-san, we veterans have to stick in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Kuwabara, you defended your Honinbou\Ntitle successfully against Kurata-kun didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.86,0:14:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear Ichiryuu-san and Hatanaka-kun will be\Ncompeting in the Meijin match next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.37,0:14:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Ichiryuu-san will cut apart\Nthat young Hatanaka boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.46,0:14:59.21,Background,,0,0,0,,We can't let these young ones take the world yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.91,0:15:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me Master Kuwabara, but Master\NOgata already has two titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was satisfied with just Honinbou...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.46,0:15:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but I may have to seriously try to get the Gosei\Nand Jyudan titles if Ogata-kun holds them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.19,0:15:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had pretty good luck against Ogata-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.04,0:15:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Ogata-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.92,0:15:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting for you in the defender's chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:41.30,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Oh no... he's gaining confidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.71,0:15:44.00,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Master Ogata...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:46.59,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fs37\1c&H246F97&\bord0\shad2\frz330\frx2\fry6\pos(443,167)}Japanese Go Institute
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.31,0:15:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.40,0:15:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.61,0:16:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been less than two years since I played\Nyou in the new first dan series.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.99,0:16:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I defeated you even with a reverse\Nkomi handicap of five and a half moku.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.02,0:16:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was that much better than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're playing an even game today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me how much you've improved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.30,0:16:31.62,Thinking,,0,0,0,,I recorded that new first dan series game, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.52,0:16:34.85,Thinking,,0,0,0,,It's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.61,0:16:39.81,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Touya-kun was a new first dan just awhile ago,\Nand he's already in the Honinbou league.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.35,0:16:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, publishing section.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.33,0:16:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Miyake-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.04,0:16:58.75,Background,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Really!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay... I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.20,0:17:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Miyake? Miyake-san from Maichou\Nnewspaper? What was it about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.47,0:17:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Master T-Touya Kouyou has signed a contract\Nwith the Bei'jing team of China!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.31,0:17:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Bei'jing team?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.58,0:17:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bei'jing team in China's team league?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.12,0:17:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Team league?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.15,0:17:34.41,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fad(334,334)}Translator's Note: J-league is a Japanese soccer thing. I don't\Nplay soccer. I don't play baseball either. I won't comment any\Nmore on J-league in fear of pulling another carps fiasco.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.77,0:17:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,China has something similar\Nto Japan's J-league for Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that there were teams who had contracts\Nwith top Korean players, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.37,0:17:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.54,0:17:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.75,0:17:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that Master Touya has retired, he's\Nfree from Japan's match schedule!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.28,0:17:48.84,Background,,0,0,0,,China's contracts don't pay\Nvery much for a Japanese,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but for Master Touya,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the benefit of getting to play against the best\Nplayers in the world must be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoshikawa-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.60,0:17:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Master Touya now! Get his comments on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.10,0:18:03.73,NoteArial,,0,0,10,,{\fs20\1c&H7AE4D7&\3c&H1C758E&\alpha&H40&\bord1\shad0.5}China Go Institute
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:06.27,Background,,0,0,0,,Yang Hai!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.71,0:18:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.23,0:18:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Touya from Japan just\Njoined the Bei'jing team!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. There's already a commotion\Nabout it on the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.07,0:18:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes the Bei'jing team a lot stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.87,0:18:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The team league is going to\Nget a lot more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.60,0:18:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Shang'hai team, that Wang Xing\Nand I are in, is going to be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.32,0:18:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem happy. Aren't you a Touya Kouyou fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.59,0:18:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! He's closest to mastering the divine move!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.55,0:18:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The divine move, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.97,0:18:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The divine move will be born in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.69,0:18:45.23,Background,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.73,0:18:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't they say it'll take a century before\Ncomputers can beat people at Go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.88,0:18:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't need a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.15,0:18:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I found a sponsor for the project. I can start now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.68,0:18:59.58,Background,,0,0,0,,We've already started inputting\Nthe data somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.35,0:19:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.64,0:19:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Bei'jing team is weak because\Nyou're always doing crap like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! This has nothing to do with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At least my own win rate is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.25,0:19:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Worse than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.66,0:19:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get through. No one's picking\Nup at Master Touya's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked a few Chinese websites. It's for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:31.86,Thinking,,0,0,0,,I saw Akira-kun this morning, but he didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:34.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,I wonder if he knows anything about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he joined the Bei'jing team...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.45,0:19:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,this means that Master Touya will be going\Nto China regularly from now on, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.33,0:19:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many games he has every\Nyear... I should check up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Weekly Go's going to have to follow\Nup on that from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.47,0:19:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to get busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Amano-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.88,0:19:54.67,Background,,0,0,0,,Amano-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.64,0:20:00.43,Background,,0,0,0,,Yoshikawa-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.95,0:20:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.49,0:20:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it feel like the Go world is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.19,0:20:09.10,Background,,0,0,0,,moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.65,0:20:11.02,Background,,0,0,0,,The whole Go world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.48,0:20:23.33,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Touya.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.63,0:20:31.63,Thinking,,0,0,0,,I want to play you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:33.04,Thinking,,0,0,0,,As soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.06,0:20:38.97,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Against you. As soon as possible.
